est for cross-country skiers.\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 809, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2021, Diggins became the first man or woman from outside Europe to win a Tour.\", \"from\": 810, \"to\": 891, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 822, \"end\": 829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skylar_Diggins-Smith\", \"score\": 0.9999969396657423, \"rank\": 3.0603432315284e-06, \"text\": \"Diggins\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skylar_Diggins-Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skylar_Diggins-Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last season, she won it for a second time.\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 934, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Both seasons, Diggins also won the season-long World Cup overall title, crowning her the world's top cross-country skier.\", \"from\": 936, \"to\": 1057, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 953, \"end\": 960, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skylar_Diggins-Smith\", \"score\": 0.9999969396657423, \"rank\": 3.0603432315284e-06, \"text\": \"Diggins\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skylar_Diggins-Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skylar_Diggins-Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eighteen of Diggins' 21 career individual World Cup race wins have come in distance events.\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1150, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1074, \"end\": 1081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skylar_Diggins-Smith\", \"score\": 0.9999969396657423, \"rank\": 3.0603432315284e-06, \"text\": \"Diggins\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skylar_Diggins-Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Skylar_Diggins-Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She also has one World Cup victory each in a relay and a team sprint, plus her two Tour de Ski titles count as World Cup wins.\", \"from\": 1151,